1
00:00:07,549 --> 00:00:10,511
HAENGBOK PAWNSHOP

2
00:00:57,599 --> 00:00:58,976
What...

3
00:01:09,278 --> 00:01:10,445
Oh, shit.

4
00:01:21,415 --> 00:01:22,416
Hey!

5
00:01:25,669 --> 00:01:26,795
Woogy, hey.

6
00:01:28,589 --> 00:01:30,465
Hey! Woogy!

7
00:01:31,466 --> 00:01:32,634
Wake up! Come on!

8
00:01:33,427 --> 00:01:34,678
Hey!

9
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:38,849
Hey, what--what happened?
Why are you here?

10
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:39,975
What the hell is going on?

11
00:01:46,023 --> 00:01:47,024
Huh?

12
00:01:48,859 --> 00:01:50,569
Wh--What?

13
00:01:51,403 --> 00:01:53,405
-I asked you what you were doing here.
-I...

14
00:01:54,990 --> 00:01:57,326
The--the--the potatoes.

15
00:01:58,118 --> 00:01:59,536
The gold bars.

16
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:01,163
Oh! Lee Dokyung! Oh!

17
00:02:01,955 --> 00:02:03,582
What?

18
00:02:13,842 --> 00:02:14,843
I didn't do it.

19
00:02:15,761 --> 00:02:17,387
Seriously, I really didn't do it!

20
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:19,598
Lee Dokyung showed up here and...

21
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:23,060
He shot me.
Wait, I got shot.

22
00:02:23,143 --> 00:02:25,937
-Ah, shit.
Huh? How am I alive right now?

23
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:29,983
Wait, what is this?

24
00:02:30,067 --> 00:02:32,277
Where are the bars?

25
00:02:33,195 --> 00:02:34,696
Heeju, I told you I didn't do anything.

26
00:02:36,114 --> 00:02:37,199
I really didn't take the gold!

27
00:02:37,282 --> 00:02:39,951
I mean, yeah, I came here to get it,
but then Lee Dokyung got to it.

28
00:02:40,452 --> 00:02:43,038
Wait, wait, wait!
What time is it?

29
00:02:44,539 --> 00:02:45,540
-Come here!
-Huh?

30
00:02:45,624 --> 00:02:47,209
-No time to explain! Come on!
-What? Why?

31
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:57,761
Hey, go check it out.

32
00:03:00,764 --> 00:03:01,765
What?

33
00:03:02,307 --> 00:03:04,434
Heeju, my car.
Go to my car.

34
00:03:04,518 --> 00:03:06,603
-Let's go.
-We're clear!

35
00:03:26,081 --> 00:03:27,499
By the way.

36
00:03:27,582 --> 00:03:29,292
How did you get away from Detective Kim?

37
00:03:30,752 --> 00:03:34,172
He let me go after
I gave him two gold bars.

38
00:03:34,256 --> 00:03:35,549
What? Really?

39
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:37,843
A couple of gold bars and he lets you go?

40
00:03:37,926 --> 00:03:39,344
He didn't seem like that kinda guy.

41
00:03:41,012 --> 00:03:42,681
Well apparently he is.

42
00:03:42,806 --> 00:03:46,393
If I had kept my mouth shut until the end,
he wouldn't have even gotten that.

43
00:03:46,476 --> 00:03:48,395
I thought you were done
with Lee Dokyung, though.

44
00:03:48,478 --> 00:03:49,896
Why'd you tell him where the bars were?

45
00:03:52,816 --> 00:03:54,651
Oh, yeah.

46
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:02,242
-Heeju. Here. Check this out.
-What is it?

47
00:04:02,325 --> 00:04:03,577
Huh? It's a dash cam.

48
00:04:04,536 --> 00:04:07,789
It must have caught that asshole
Lee Dokyung leaving the pawnshop.

49
00:04:08,331 --> 00:04:11,460
I mean, there's no way he just walked off
with all those gold bars on foot.

50
00:04:15,422 --> 00:04:16,923
What? Did you find something?

51
00:04:17,757 --> 00:04:18,884
Yeah.

52
00:04:18,967 --> 00:04:21,344
It looks like he's driving away in
a white car.

53
00:04:21,428 --> 00:04:23,847
Damn. I knew that asshole
would do this.

54
00:04:23,930 --> 00:04:25,891
How does it feel
to see his true colors?

55
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:27,934
Pretty shitty, right?

56
00:04:32,314 --> 00:04:35,400
Okay. First thing we need to do
is find Lee Dokyung

57
00:04:35,484 --> 00:04:37,319
before he runs off with our gold bars.

58
00:04:44,534 --> 00:04:46,912
Right now I have Kim Heeju
here in custody.

59
00:04:47,662 --> 00:04:49,289
But I think I can release her.

60
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,124
How about this?

61
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:53,210
We should make a deal.

62
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:15,023
LUCKY JEWELRY WHOLESALE

63
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:32,624
Okay.

64
00:05:35,877 --> 00:05:39,840
So I heard you guys pay cash on
the spot here. Is that right?

65
00:05:39,923 --> 00:05:46,012
Uh, yeah, we do. Though, uh, it's going
to take a moment to get it ready.

66
00:05:46,096 --> 00:05:47,639
It's quite a lot of money.

67
00:05:48,390 --> 00:05:49,391
How long?

68
00:05:49,474 --> 00:05:53,436
Uh, I'd say an hour.
Uh, maybe 30 minutes.

69
00:05:54,229 --> 00:05:56,481
-Please do it as fast as you can.
-Yes, certainly.

70
00:05:56,565 --> 00:05:59,317
How about we get you
a cup of tea while you wait?

71
00:05:59,401 --> 00:06:00,694
Hey, Yeonju?

72
00:06:00,777 --> 00:06:02,946
Would you bring this gentleman
some tea, please?

73
00:06:03,029 --> 00:06:04,072
Yes, sir.

74
00:06:25,552 --> 00:06:27,846
YES MONEY PRESIDENT KO GITAE
HE CAME.

75
00:06:27,929 --> 00:06:29,014
He's here.

76
00:06:30,974 --> 00:06:32,809
Oh. He's there! He's there!

77
00:06:33,143 --> 00:06:34,978
This has to be Lee Dokyung, right?

78
00:06:36,104 --> 00:06:38,148
Kim Jinman wasn't bullshitting, huh?

79
00:06:39,065 --> 00:06:40,483
You had guys surround it, right?

80
00:06:40,567 --> 00:06:41,568
Yeah, of course.

81
00:06:43,945 --> 00:06:44,946
Yeah, hey.

82
00:06:45,989 --> 00:06:47,824
Shut the place down
and keep that asshole inside.

83
00:06:47,908 --> 00:06:48,909
We'll be right over.

84
00:06:49,868 --> 00:06:50,910
Yeah, okay.

85
00:06:52,579 --> 00:06:53,580
Come on.

86
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:01,087
Who said you get to decide what we do?

87
00:07:14,309 --> 00:07:16,936
So, uh, well, about the gold.

88
00:07:17,312 --> 00:07:19,689
You really sure you
wanna give Kim Jinman any?

89
00:07:19,773 --> 00:07:21,524
I mean, you're the one doing all the work.

90
00:07:22,776 --> 00:07:24,402
Let's find the casket first.

91
00:07:24,486 --> 00:07:26,988
I'll need someone to clean up once
we take care of Chairman Ahn.

92
00:07:37,165 --> 00:07:39,209
Hello. Welcome...

93
00:07:47,509 --> 00:07:49,219
Who the hell are--

94
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:11,157
Yes, boss.

95
00:08:11,241 --> 00:08:12,492
It's Lee Dokyung.

96
00:08:13,243 --> 00:08:14,452
Cool. Good work.

97
00:08:16,162 --> 00:08:18,665
They checked his passport.
It's Lee Dokyung.

98
00:08:19,124 --> 00:08:20,750
Boss, we've finally found him!

99
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:30,927
Where's Lee Dokyung?

100
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:32,137
He's right over here, sir.

101
00:08:42,272 --> 00:08:45,275
Oh, man.
This wasn't necessary.

102
00:08:45,358 --> 00:08:46,359
Just hold still.

103
00:08:48,319 --> 00:08:51,156
Captain. It's been a while.

104
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:55,368
I was always gonna find you.

105
00:08:55,452 --> 00:08:57,537
There was really no need
for all the fuss.

106
00:08:59,622 --> 00:09:00,874
Where's the casket?

107
00:09:19,642 --> 00:09:21,478
I--I don't know.

108
00:09:22,020 --> 00:09:24,481
Do you really mean that?
You don't know?

109
00:09:25,065 --> 00:09:26,483
Or you just don't feel like saying?

110
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:29,652
Ah, shit.
I--I--I really don't know.

111
00:09:31,696 --> 00:09:32,906
Tell me who does.

112
00:09:34,699 --> 00:09:35,784
Kim Heeju?

113
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:38,745
Tell me.

114
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:42,290
Before I peel your whole face off.

115
00:09:48,088 --> 00:09:50,131
Heeju. Hee--Heeju.

116
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:52,467
Heeju never told me where it is.

117
00:09:53,802 --> 00:09:54,969
I mean it.

118
00:09:57,305 --> 00:09:58,765
Well, that was fast.

119
00:09:59,516 --> 00:10:00,892
I haven't even started.

120
00:10:04,437 --> 00:10:08,191
So Kim Heeju knows where it is,
but you claim you don't.

121
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:12,529
Even though you're dating?

122
00:10:15,490 --> 00:10:17,200
Heeju doesn't trust me now.

123
00:10:18,827 --> 00:10:20,912
We broke up
and I can't even reach her anymore.

124
00:10:22,038 --> 00:10:23,039
Really?

125
00:10:24,499 --> 00:10:25,500
Bullshit.

126
00:10:33,216 --> 00:10:34,843
Why don't you call Kim Heeju, then?

127
00:10:36,427 --> 00:10:38,638
Call her and get her to come here.

128
00:10:40,056 --> 00:10:42,016
Then maybe I'll spare your life,
Captain.

129
00:11:33,818 --> 00:11:38,031
EPISODE 10
GOLD LAND

130
00:11:57,258 --> 00:11:58,259
INCOMING CALL

131
00:11:58,343 --> 00:11:59,594
Who is it? Detective Kim?

132
00:11:59,677 --> 00:12:00,845
No.

133
00:12:03,181 --> 00:12:04,515
It's Lee Dokyung.

134
00:12:06,184 --> 00:12:07,185
Lee Dokyung?

135
00:12:08,686 --> 00:12:10,855
You should pick up.
Find out where the gold bars are.

136
00:12:10,939 --> 00:12:12,815
Yeah, but he thinks I'm in custody,

137
00:12:12,899 --> 00:12:15,401
so he would expect Detective Kim
to answer.

138
00:12:16,319 --> 00:12:21,282
But then if he's expecting Detective Kim,
then why would he even try to call me?

139
00:12:23,243 --> 00:12:24,661
I--it doesn't matter.
Just pick up.

140
00:12:28,081 --> 00:12:29,082
Hey Heeju.

141
00:12:30,291 --> 00:12:32,585
I'm at Lucky Jewelry
in Daejeong right now.

142
00:12:34,254 --> 00:12:38,091
I'm looking at some wedding rings for us.
Can you come over here?

143
00:12:39,175 --> 00:12:40,176
Huh?

144
00:12:40,969 --> 00:12:42,011
What do you mean?

145
00:12:42,595 --> 00:12:43,596
Heeju!

146
00:12:45,682 --> 00:12:47,350
How are you able to answer the phone?

147
00:12:50,853 --> 00:12:53,648
Heeju, don't come here no matter what!
You hear me? Heeju!

148
00:12:53,731 --> 00:12:55,692
I'll get right to the point, Kim Heeju.

149
00:12:55,775 --> 00:12:56,776
Where is the casket?

150
00:12:58,278 --> 00:13:00,697
If you tell me right now,
I'll spare Lee Dokyung's life.

151
00:13:01,447 --> 00:13:02,824
But I'll kill him if you don't.

152
00:13:04,951 --> 00:13:07,578
Cha Yujin told you where it was
and you still killed her anyway.

153
00:13:08,079 --> 00:13:09,205
You're right.

154
00:13:13,793 --> 00:13:15,128
What should I do?

155
00:13:16,337 --> 00:13:18,798
I really would like the captain to live.

156
00:13:22,969 --> 00:13:24,637
What if I bring the casket to you?

157
00:13:25,555 --> 00:13:26,597
Really?

158
00:13:27,307 --> 00:13:29,225
Yeah, I'll give you the casket.
I really will.

159
00:13:29,726 --> 00:13:31,019
So please let him go.

160
00:13:31,936 --> 00:13:34,605
Yeah. Yeah, of course.

161
00:13:35,273 --> 00:13:36,691
Uh, what time can I meet you?

162
00:13:36,774 --> 00:13:38,067
You're in Jeongsan, right?

163
00:13:38,609 --> 00:13:40,820
So then let me think.
Two, three hours...

164
00:13:41,362 --> 00:13:42,447
Let's meet around midnight.

165
00:13:42,989 --> 00:13:44,073
Okay.

166
00:13:44,157 --> 00:13:45,575
If you don't show up
by midnight...

167
00:13:46,159 --> 00:13:48,411
...I'll skin Lee Dokyung alive.

168
00:13:50,913 --> 00:13:51,956
Heeju.

169
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:55,293
Why would you tell him that?

170
00:13:56,377 --> 00:13:57,420
Huh?

171
00:13:57,503 --> 00:14:00,089
Heeju!
You need to wake up.

172
00:14:00,173 --> 00:14:02,341
Seriously, Lee Dokyung stabbed you in
the back and took all

173
00:14:02,425 --> 00:14:04,052
of the gold bars for himself.

174
00:14:04,135 --> 00:14:05,428
And he shot me, too!

175
00:14:06,345 --> 00:14:08,306
We shouldn't be worried whether
Lee Dokyung lives or dies.

176
00:14:08,389 --> 00:14:10,308
We need to worry about saving ourselves!

177
00:14:12,935 --> 00:14:14,979
How long would it take to get
to Daejong from here?

178
00:14:16,731 --> 00:14:19,067
I don't know.
Hour and a half, if we're fast.

179
00:14:21,194 --> 00:14:23,821
Lee Dokyung must have parked
the car close to Lucky Jewelry.

180
00:14:25,031 --> 00:14:27,533
And Park said he'd keep him alive
until midnight.

181
00:14:28,159 --> 00:14:30,745
So all we have to do is find where
he parked the car by then.

182
00:14:31,746 --> 00:14:33,289
The gold bars have to be in there.

183
00:14:33,372 --> 00:14:35,458
Oh. Okay.

184
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:38,002
Let's go, then.
I'll pull the car around.

185
00:15:27,260 --> 00:15:30,888
Lucky Jewelry is on
the back street over there.

186
00:15:30,972 --> 00:15:33,808
There's no room to park there, though,
so he must have parked around here.

187
00:15:35,351 --> 00:15:37,645
You check the streets over there.
I'll go that way.

188
00:15:38,896 --> 00:15:40,022
We're not going together?

189
00:15:40,815 --> 00:15:42,150
We don't have time for that.

190
00:15:43,734 --> 00:15:44,735
Heeju.

191
00:15:45,862 --> 00:15:48,781
If one of us gets captured by Yes Money...

192
00:15:49,699 --> 00:15:52,201
...let's save the other even if we have
to give up the gold.

193
00:15:53,286 --> 00:15:54,537
I won't agree to that.

194
00:15:55,580 --> 00:15:56,664
No.

195
00:15:56,747 --> 00:15:58,916
I don't want to live if we have
to give up the gold.

196
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,294
I don't.
I'd rather just die.

197
00:16:03,254 --> 00:16:05,131
I'd still feel the same
if you got caught.

198
00:16:08,092 --> 00:16:09,093
Okay.

199
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:10,761
Be safe.

200
00:16:57,225 --> 00:16:59,393
One five one four.
One five one four.

201
00:17:15,451 --> 00:17:17,078
Hey, asshole.

202
00:17:17,995 --> 00:17:20,623
I told you I never wanted
to see your face again, didn't I?

203
00:17:21,207 --> 00:17:23,793
In fact, I said I'd kill you
if I ever saw you around.

204
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:24,877
Remember that, asshole?

205
00:17:26,671 --> 00:17:27,797
What are you doing here?

206
00:17:28,881 --> 00:17:29,882
What's with this car?

207
00:17:30,383 --> 00:17:32,051
It's Lee Dokyung's.

208
00:17:32,843 --> 00:17:34,136
And? What's in it?

209
00:17:37,682 --> 00:17:38,891
The gold bars?

210
00:17:40,434 --> 00:17:41,435
Yeah.

211
00:17:43,354 --> 00:17:44,689
Okay.

212
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:46,566
Well, what are you waiting for? Go.

213
00:18:00,705 --> 00:18:03,457
Whose gold bars are they?
Kim Heeju's or Lee Dokyung's?

214
00:18:03,749 --> 00:18:04,750
Kim Heeju's.

215
00:18:08,254 --> 00:18:10,548
Lee Dokyung stole hers
from the pawnshop earlier.

216
00:18:12,216 --> 00:18:14,051
Where's Kim Heeju, then?

217
00:18:14,802 --> 00:18:15,970
Didn't she come here with you?

218
00:18:16,971 --> 00:18:18,514
She's looking across the street.

219
00:18:20,141 --> 00:18:22,393
Shit. Where are they?

220
00:18:22,476 --> 00:18:24,520
Wait, how about you call Kim Heeju first?
Come on.

221
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:27,773
I said call Kim Heeju now,
asshole!

222
00:18:27,857 --> 00:18:30,234
Fuck, okay, fine. Geez.

223
00:18:33,571 --> 00:18:35,156
Why aren't they here?

224
00:18:37,908 --> 00:18:39,577
Ah, shit, where could they be?

225
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:44,123
She's not answering.

226
00:18:44,206 --> 00:18:46,709
How did you guys know Lee Dokyung's car
was going to be here?

227
00:18:46,792 --> 00:18:49,754
Well, he called us and told us
to come meet him in Daejeong.

228
00:18:50,338 --> 00:18:51,714
At Lucky Jewelry, you mean?

229
00:18:52,923 --> 00:18:54,091
Yeah, how did you know about that?

230
00:18:54,175 --> 00:18:57,720
Ah, fuck's sake!
Dammit!

231
00:18:58,304 --> 00:19:01,182
Those motherfuckers told Heeju
to bring the gold bars to them

232
00:19:01,265 --> 00:19:02,642
or they'd kill Lee Dokyung.

233
00:19:02,725 --> 00:19:04,435
So you're saying she's trying
to save Lee Dokyung?

234
00:19:04,518 --> 00:19:05,645
That's the reason she came here?

235
00:19:05,728 --> 00:19:08,522
No, we're looking for Lee Dokyung's car
to find the gold bars he stole!

236
00:19:09,065 --> 00:19:11,025
There are no gold bars, you idiot!

237
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:14,362
Did you see all the gold bars
at the pawnshop earlier?

238
00:19:14,779 --> 00:19:17,031
-I definitely did.
-You saw all the bars?

239
00:19:17,114 --> 00:19:19,575
Are you sure?
Are you 100% positive, asshole?

240
00:19:24,080 --> 00:19:25,164
Ah, shit.

241
00:19:26,332 --> 00:19:27,750
Fuck, it's here.

242
00:19:28,459 --> 00:19:30,169
Ah, I guess I didn't.

243
00:19:31,671 --> 00:19:33,297
There was only one bar in there.

244
00:19:33,381 --> 00:19:34,715
Wait a minute.

245
00:19:34,799 --> 00:19:36,509
Wait a minute.
Oh, fuck.

246
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:55,319
LUCKY JEWELRY

247
00:20:03,119 --> 00:20:05,079
JANGGAK TRADING

248
00:20:20,928 --> 00:20:23,055
When I said I hope you find happiness...

249
00:20:24,849 --> 00:20:26,100
...I really did mean it.

250
00:20:27,226 --> 00:20:28,644
But then in a way...

251
00:20:30,438 --> 00:20:32,898
...I also said that
for my own peace of mind.

252
00:20:33,858 --> 00:20:36,068
Because I don't think I
could be truly happy...

253
00:20:37,153 --> 00:20:41,741
...if everyone else was feeling miserable
and I wasn't.

254
00:20:44,618 --> 00:20:46,620
And I guess that's what I really mean.

255
00:20:47,997 --> 00:20:51,959
So from now on,
you should just think about yourself.

256
00:21:40,841 --> 00:21:42,468
It's almost midnight now.

257
00:21:43,219 --> 00:21:44,929
You think Kim Heeju will show up?

258
00:21:46,764 --> 00:21:48,849
I think Lee Dokyung
was telling the truth.

259
00:21:49,642 --> 00:21:51,477
That asshole doesn't know where
the casket is.

260
00:21:53,646 --> 00:21:54,855
She'll show.

261
00:21:57,024 --> 00:21:58,025
Alone?

262
00:21:58,609 --> 00:21:59,610
Mm.

263
00:22:00,528 --> 00:22:01,529
With the casket?

264
00:22:02,071 --> 00:22:03,906
How would she carry that on her own?

265
00:22:05,616 --> 00:22:08,035
She'll probably have it in her car
and pull up over here.

266
00:22:09,537 --> 00:22:10,996
Or she won't bring it.

267
00:22:12,081 --> 00:22:13,332
What if she doesn't?

268
00:22:15,292 --> 00:22:17,211
Then we'll fucking make her talk.

269
00:22:17,461 --> 00:22:18,462
Right.

270
00:22:19,547 --> 00:22:23,425
Well, if she talks,
it'll be easy from there.

271
00:22:31,433 --> 00:22:32,434
Easy?

272
00:22:34,645 --> 00:22:36,522
-Gitae.
-Yes, sir?

273
00:22:38,732 --> 00:22:39,859
Let me see your phone.

274
00:22:39,942 --> 00:22:40,943
What?

275
00:22:42,319 --> 00:22:43,571
What do you need my phone for?

276
00:22:43,654 --> 00:22:47,449
I just need to make sure you haven't been
in contact with Chairman Ahn, is all.

277
00:22:48,450 --> 00:22:50,035
I need to know I can really trust you.

278
00:22:57,710 --> 00:22:58,836
Wow.

279
00:23:00,921 --> 00:23:03,173
This is kind of fucked up, you know.

280
00:23:05,092 --> 00:23:06,719
Seriously, come on!

281
00:23:07,636 --> 00:23:09,388
I mean, this is going a little too far.

282
00:23:14,685 --> 00:23:17,021
Fine. I--I hear you.
I'll show you, all right?

283
00:23:17,104 --> 00:23:18,314
Here, gimme a second.

284
00:23:19,565 --> 00:23:20,774
See? No problem, okay?

285
00:23:21,609 --> 00:23:22,818
I already unlocked it.

286
00:23:59,521 --> 00:24:00,564
CHAIRMAN AHN

287
00:24:00,648 --> 00:24:04,443
I'm heading to Daejeong with Park.
It's Lee Dokyung.

288
00:24:04,526 --> 00:24:07,947
Kim Heeju agreed to bring
the casket to Daejeong by midnight.

289
00:24:08,739 --> 00:24:11,575
Keep all three
of them alive. I'm arriving soon.

290
00:24:11,951 --> 00:24:13,744
This fucker.

291
00:24:24,463 --> 00:24:25,631
Fuck.

292
00:24:37,935 --> 00:24:39,853
-I think she took the gun.
-What?

293
00:24:41,563 --> 00:24:42,564
Shit.

294
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:45,526
Wait a minute!
Wait a minute.

295
00:24:46,860 --> 00:24:48,237
The dash cam.

296
00:24:54,410 --> 00:24:57,788
-W--w--wait. But that's not--
-What? What is it?

297
00:24:58,706 --> 00:25:00,958
The gold bars wouldn't fit
in that.

298
00:25:01,583 --> 00:25:03,419
What are you talking about?

299
00:25:03,502 --> 00:25:04,920
That bag is too small.

300
00:25:06,672 --> 00:25:08,716
There was only one bar
at the pawnshop, then.

301
00:25:10,342 --> 00:25:12,720
Oh, Kim Heeju, you little...

302
00:25:16,557 --> 00:25:18,017
Hey, the jewelry shop.

303
00:25:19,435 --> 00:25:20,686
Oh, shit.

304
00:25:28,444 --> 00:25:30,863
Sir, what--
what's with the blood?

305
00:25:30,946 --> 00:25:33,282
-Huh?
-Where's President Ko?

306
00:25:34,241 --> 00:25:35,617
Having a smoke.

307
00:25:36,618 --> 00:25:40,456
Do any of you have any idea what's inside
the casket? Huh?

308
00:25:41,373 --> 00:25:43,834
Ko didn't mention anything
to you guys at all?

309
00:25:43,917 --> 00:25:44,918
Is it...

310
00:25:45,586 --> 00:25:47,421
...drugs or something?

311
00:25:47,504 --> 00:25:48,505
It's not.

312
00:25:50,466 --> 00:25:51,759
Gold bars!

313
00:25:53,802 --> 00:25:56,221
10-kilo gold bars!

314
00:26:00,934 --> 00:26:02,478
100 of 'em!

315
00:26:04,605 --> 00:26:06,440
At least you'll die knowing the truth.

316
00:26:06,523 --> 00:26:08,567
-What?
-Huh?

317
00:26:08,650 --> 00:26:10,944
-Oh, shit.
-You motherfucker.

318
00:26:13,572 --> 00:26:14,573
Asshole!

319
00:27:18,387 --> 00:27:20,764
Hey. This isn't gonna work.

320
00:27:21,223 --> 00:27:22,516
Bring the car around for us.

321
00:27:22,599 --> 00:27:23,976
No. Let me go with you.

322
00:27:24,059 --> 00:27:25,978
No, no, no. I'll get Kim Heeju.
You get the car.

323
00:27:26,061 --> 00:27:27,980
Pull the car around and wait.
There's no time.

324
00:27:28,063 --> 00:27:29,147
Chairman Ahn's on his way.
Hurry.

325
00:27:29,231 --> 00:27:30,274
Go.

326
00:28:01,513 --> 00:28:02,764
Hey, are you okay?

327
00:28:05,934 --> 00:28:07,519
-Are you okay?
-Heeju. Heeju.

328
00:28:07,895 --> 00:28:09,855
Let's get out of here first.
Can you stand?

329
00:28:13,775 --> 00:28:15,027
Be careful.

330
00:28:23,368 --> 00:28:24,703
You fucker!

331
00:28:46,558 --> 00:28:48,352
Shit.

332
00:28:59,363 --> 00:29:00,656
Fuck.

333
00:29:05,535 --> 00:29:08,163
You almost killed me, you fucking bitch.

334
00:29:37,776 --> 00:29:39,069
Please wait here for a minute, sir.

335
00:29:39,152 --> 00:29:40,487
I'll take care of it and be right back.

336
00:29:40,570 --> 00:29:42,739
Don't leave any bodies behind.

337
00:29:43,448 --> 00:29:45,784
I want you to bring all three
of them alive.

338
00:29:45,867 --> 00:29:47,285
Three, sir?

339
00:29:47,744 --> 00:29:52,249
Ju Haran, Lee Dokyung, Park Hocheol.

340
00:29:52,332 --> 00:29:54,001
Yes. I'll bring them to you.

341
00:29:54,710 --> 00:29:56,503
Okay. Let's go.

342
00:29:56,586 --> 00:29:57,879
Yes, sir.

343
00:30:01,341 --> 00:30:04,094
We don't have a lot of time.
Where's the gold?

344
00:30:06,722 --> 00:30:07,723
Captain.

345
00:30:09,307 --> 00:30:10,600
Do you really not know?

346
00:30:12,644 --> 00:30:13,729
Huh?

347
00:30:14,479 --> 00:30:16,273
Kim Heeju, you know where they are.

348
00:30:17,232 --> 00:30:19,026
Bitch, just fucking tell me!

349
00:30:19,526 --> 00:30:21,361
Hee--Heeju, don't tell him anything!

350
00:30:21,695 --> 00:30:24,114
Don't do it!
If you tell him, he'll kill us both!

351
00:30:24,197 --> 00:30:27,242
If you don't tell him,
he m--he might spare you, Heeju!

352
00:30:33,623 --> 00:30:35,333
Captain, you really don't know.

353
00:30:36,418 --> 00:30:37,419
Right?

354
00:31:00,692 --> 00:31:02,402
He's right about one thing,
though.

355
00:31:03,570 --> 00:31:08,200
Now the only person who knows where
the casket is, is you, Kim Heeju.

356
00:31:08,283 --> 00:31:10,911
If you don't tell me,
I can't kill you.

357
00:31:10,994 --> 00:31:14,247
But you should know it'll be
way more painful to live.

358
00:31:16,583 --> 00:31:18,752
And I'll make sure you live
until you talk.

359
00:31:20,378 --> 00:31:21,379
You bitch!

360
00:31:23,673 --> 00:31:24,758
Fuck.

361
00:31:32,974 --> 00:31:34,267
Where's the casket?

362
00:31:37,437 --> 00:31:39,731
Tell me where it is!

363
00:31:39,815 --> 00:31:41,733
For fuck's sake!

364
00:31:41,817 --> 00:31:44,236
Dammit. Tell me!

365
00:31:44,319 --> 00:31:46,780
Where's the fucking casket?

366
00:31:48,782 --> 00:31:51,701
Dammit. You fucking bitch!

367
00:32:02,921 --> 00:32:04,172
Shit.

368
00:32:20,981 --> 00:32:22,232
Who the hell was that?

369
00:32:25,360 --> 00:32:26,778
Get this shit out
of the way!

370
00:32:26,862 --> 00:32:27,946
Come on!

371
00:32:32,033 --> 00:32:34,494
-Come on! Get this off!
-Come on!

372
00:32:40,167 --> 00:32:41,626
One, two!

373
00:32:49,259 --> 00:32:50,343
Kim Heeju!

374
00:32:51,261 --> 00:32:53,471
Are you all right? Hey!

375
00:32:53,555 --> 00:32:54,890
Kim Heeju!

376
00:33:05,650 --> 00:33:06,985
Shit.

377
00:33:16,870 --> 00:33:18,163
Fuck me!

378
00:34:19,599 --> 00:34:21,977
You fucking bitch.

379
00:34:25,814 --> 00:34:26,815
You...

380
00:34:43,707 --> 00:34:44,958
Hey! Kim Heeju!

381
00:34:45,458 --> 00:34:47,002
Ah, shit!

382
00:34:52,716 --> 00:34:53,925
Hang in there.

383
00:34:55,552 --> 00:34:56,636
What the...

384
00:34:58,597 --> 00:34:59,848
Heeju!

385
00:35:00,390 --> 00:35:01,433
Are you okay?

386
00:35:02,851 --> 00:35:03,977
Did you get shot?

387
00:35:04,561 --> 00:35:05,895
Detective.

388
00:35:05,979 --> 00:35:07,314
I held off the Geumseong guys
for a little,

389
00:35:07,397 --> 00:35:08,440
but they'll be here any minute.

390
00:35:08,815 --> 00:35:10,567
Ah, fuckin' hell.

391
00:35:10,650 --> 00:35:11,818
Hey, stay with me.

392
00:35:12,235 --> 00:35:13,320
The workshop.

393
00:35:14,321 --> 00:35:15,447
What?

394
00:35:16,323 --> 00:35:17,574
The gold bars.

395
00:35:18,283 --> 00:35:20,035
Jeil Workshop.

396
00:35:21,620 --> 00:35:22,621
Oh, dammit.

397
00:35:23,580 --> 00:35:24,914
Oh, fuck.

398
00:35:27,500 --> 00:35:28,585
Oh, shit!

399
00:35:34,716 --> 00:35:35,967
Am I gonna make it?

400
00:35:37,510 --> 00:35:38,845
I just want...

401
00:35:42,515 --> 00:35:44,184
...to live a normal life.

402
00:35:47,562 --> 00:35:50,857
Just a--just a normal life.

403
00:35:59,741 --> 00:36:00,825
You won't die.

404
00:36:02,535 --> 00:36:03,870
You just have to hang in there.

405
00:36:04,496 --> 00:36:05,830
Just hold on!

406
00:36:09,417 --> 00:36:10,543
Keep holding on.

407
00:37:02,721 --> 00:37:05,223
Come on. Come on.

408
00:37:25,702 --> 00:37:28,121
Ah, fuck.

409
00:37:54,731 --> 00:37:56,232
Oh, shit.

410
00:38:00,528 --> 00:38:02,655
Heh, son of a bitch.

411
00:38:03,239 --> 00:38:05,033
-Hey, nuh-uh. Detective!
-Put it down, asshole.

412
00:38:05,116 --> 00:38:06,284
You put yours down first!

413
00:38:06,367 --> 00:38:08,161
I told you,
put the gun down, motherfucker!

414
00:38:08,244 --> 00:38:09,245
I'll shoot you!

415
00:38:09,329 --> 00:38:11,289
You're not gonna walk out
of here with that gold

416
00:38:11,372 --> 00:38:13,082
so drop the gun and call it a day.

417
00:38:13,583 --> 00:38:15,251
Detective, those gold bars?

418
00:38:15,543 --> 00:38:17,921
I'll hand them all over to Chairman Ahn
so I can get Heeju out.

419
00:38:18,004 --> 00:38:19,422
I know that's what you want, too!

420
00:38:19,506 --> 00:38:22,008
Why the hell do you care
so much about Kim Heeju?

421
00:38:22,091 --> 00:38:23,510
Is she your sister?

422
00:38:23,593 --> 00:38:25,720
No. Nothing like that.

423
00:38:25,804 --> 00:38:27,347
But we both saved each other's lives.

424
00:38:28,264 --> 00:38:29,891
Just put the gun down.

425
00:38:29,974 --> 00:38:31,184
You put your gun down first.

426
00:38:31,267 --> 00:38:33,603
-Drop the gun, you--
-Uh, e--excuse me.

427
00:38:33,686 --> 00:38:35,146
Sorry to interrupt.

428
00:38:35,230 --> 00:38:36,940
It's just that I've been listening
to you guys.

429
00:38:37,315 --> 00:38:39,192
I think there's been a misunderstanding.

430
00:38:40,151 --> 00:38:43,404
Those gold bars, well, they're fake.

431
00:38:44,697 --> 00:38:47,659
Heeju asked me to make them,
so I did it for her.

432
00:38:47,742 --> 00:38:48,868
I was up all night.

433
00:38:50,078 --> 00:38:51,246
I was wondering.

434
00:38:51,913 --> 00:38:55,834
Could you make fake gold bars
that look exactly like these ones?

435
00:38:58,962 --> 00:39:00,088
Where are the real ones?

436
00:39:00,171 --> 00:39:02,215
Sorry, but I really don't know.

437
00:39:02,715 --> 00:39:05,718
I agreed to do whatever Heeju asked me
to do. That's all.

438
00:39:07,679 --> 00:39:09,097
Dammit. Detective.

439
00:39:09,931 --> 00:39:11,224
You don't trust me, do you?

440
00:39:12,100 --> 00:39:13,726
I don't trust you, either.

441
00:39:13,810 --> 00:39:16,062
And obviously Heeju doesn't trust either
of us.

442
00:39:16,396 --> 00:39:18,106
At least it looks that way, right?

443
00:39:18,189 --> 00:39:20,358
That's why she wouldn't tell us where
the real gold bars are.

444
00:39:20,441 --> 00:39:21,901
Ah, shit.

445
00:39:22,652 --> 00:39:23,987
And you know what she told me?

446
00:39:24,404 --> 00:39:26,322
She said if she lost the gold bars...

447
00:39:26,906 --> 00:39:28,867
...she wouldn't even want to live anymore.

448
00:39:29,617 --> 00:39:31,369
That if it came to that...

449
00:39:32,412 --> 00:39:34,163
...then I should just let her die.

450
00:39:34,831 --> 00:39:38,209
Whoever she takes after,
she's fucking smart. Dammit.

451
00:40:21,502 --> 00:40:24,923
HAENGBOK PAWNSHOP

452
00:40:29,552 --> 00:40:31,304
They're not in the pawnshop, sir.

453
00:40:37,560 --> 00:40:39,854
Who else knew the gold bars were there?

454
00:40:41,397 --> 00:40:42,482
Woogy?

455
00:40:42,565 --> 00:40:44,734
Did he take them?

456
00:40:46,903 --> 00:40:48,947
Or did you hide them somewhere else?

457
00:40:51,991 --> 00:40:53,868
If the gold bars aren't there...

458
00:40:55,578 --> 00:40:57,038
...I really don't know where they are.

459
00:41:01,751 --> 00:41:03,336
It's over now.

460
00:41:03,419 --> 00:41:06,297
I don't understand why you're
still making this so hard.

461
00:41:07,382 --> 00:41:10,176
It's not like dragging this out
is gonna save your life.

462
00:41:10,635 --> 00:41:14,055
The only thing you're doing
is hurting yourself.

463
00:41:17,350 --> 00:41:18,351
Understand?

464
00:41:18,935 --> 00:41:21,145
I won't guarantee I'll spare your life.

465
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:25,900
But I will pull
your guts out and shove 'em in your face

466
00:41:25,984 --> 00:41:28,778
until you talk.
And you will talk.

467
00:41:29,529 --> 00:41:30,947
Promise you that.

468
00:41:32,991 --> 00:41:34,659
I really mean it.

469
00:41:35,785 --> 00:41:36,995
I don't know.

470
00:41:38,454 --> 00:41:40,164
Mr. Jin.

471
00:41:41,791 --> 00:41:42,875
Get started.

472
00:41:43,501 --> 00:41:44,794
Yes, sir.

473
00:41:47,714 --> 00:41:51,884
No. No! No, no, please! I don't know.
I really don't.

474
00:41:51,968 --> 00:41:53,219
Please stop, please.

475
00:41:53,302 --> 00:41:57,015
I don't know!
Please stop! No! No!

476
00:41:57,724 --> 00:41:58,725
MESSAGES

477
00:41:58,808 --> 00:42:01,310
JEONGSAN KIM JINMAN

478
00:42:01,853 --> 00:42:02,937
Wait a minute.

479
00:42:05,231 --> 00:42:07,984
INCOMING CALL
JEONGSAN KIM JINMAN

480
00:42:10,153 --> 00:42:11,446
What does this mean?

481
00:42:12,030 --> 00:42:13,322
Why do you have the gold?

482
00:42:13,948 --> 00:42:15,992
Kim Heeju hid the gold bars
in the pawnshop.

483
00:42:17,201 --> 00:42:18,494
I found them earlier.

484
00:42:18,578 --> 00:42:19,996
Oh, really?

485
00:42:20,079 --> 00:42:22,540
What are you waiting for, then?
Bring them to me.

486
00:42:22,623 --> 00:42:25,126
You can keep one gold bar,
as I promised.

487
00:42:26,085 --> 00:42:28,212
First, please release her.

488
00:42:30,423 --> 00:42:31,466
Kim Heeju?

489
00:42:34,844 --> 00:42:36,512
Are you helping her?

490
00:42:37,388 --> 00:42:39,223
Then I definitely shouldn't
release her.

491
00:42:39,307 --> 00:42:40,892
How can I trust you?

492
00:42:41,517 --> 00:42:45,438
What if I let Kim Heeju go
and you made off with the gold bars?

493
00:42:45,521 --> 00:42:47,106
Meet me at the Gold Resort.

494
00:42:47,190 --> 00:42:48,399
6:00 o'clock.

495
00:42:48,858 --> 00:42:50,234
I'll bring the gold bars there.

496
00:42:51,277 --> 00:42:52,487
You can check them then.

497
00:42:53,905 --> 00:42:55,198
And release Kim Heeju.

498
00:42:56,032 --> 00:42:59,368
This whole situation
just doesn't add up.

499
00:43:00,369 --> 00:43:02,580
The gold bars are in your hands right now.

500
00:43:04,999 --> 00:43:06,793
And you're saying you'd give them up
for this girl?

501
00:43:06,876 --> 00:43:08,336
What's going on here, Detective?

502
00:43:10,254 --> 00:43:12,381
Kim Heeju is my daughter.

503
00:43:13,716 --> 00:43:15,009
Does it all make sense
to you now?

504
00:43:17,762 --> 00:43:19,597
Oh, wow!

505
00:43:21,140 --> 00:43:22,475
Is that right?

506
00:43:23,893 --> 00:43:25,144
You know what?

507
00:43:25,228 --> 00:43:26,979
Yeah, that does make sense now.

508
00:43:27,063 --> 00:43:28,940
Let me talk to her for a minute.

509
00:43:29,023 --> 00:43:30,316
I need to check if she's alive.

510
00:43:31,025 --> 00:43:32,610
Oh, no.

511
00:43:32,693 --> 00:43:34,904
What would you do if I killed her already?

512
00:43:35,738 --> 00:43:36,948
Well then I guess...

513
00:43:37,907 --> 00:43:39,492
...I can't return the gold.

514
00:43:39,575 --> 00:43:42,870
Wow, Kim Jinman acting like
a father, huh?

515
00:43:50,211 --> 00:43:51,379
Hey.

516
00:43:52,588 --> 00:43:55,591
Kim Jinman.
He says he's your father.

517
00:44:06,018 --> 00:44:07,478
Hey.

518
00:44:08,646 --> 00:44:09,647
Hey.

519
00:44:10,481 --> 00:44:11,816
Keep hanging in there.

520
00:44:11,899 --> 00:44:13,442
I'll save you.

521
00:44:22,910 --> 00:44:29,917
THE LATE YEO SUNOK

522
00:45:30,978 --> 00:45:32,146
Hey.

523
00:45:33,314 --> 00:45:34,523
Give this to Kim Heeju.

524
00:45:35,524 --> 00:45:37,068
What is it?

525
00:45:37,818 --> 00:45:39,445
Just give it to her.
She'll know.

526
00:45:40,196 --> 00:45:41,739
Why don't you give it to her yourself?

527
00:45:42,531 --> 00:45:44,784
Do as I say, little shit.

528
00:45:46,786 --> 00:45:47,912
Detective, wait.

529
00:45:49,914 --> 00:45:50,915
You up for a smoke?

530
00:45:57,088 --> 00:45:58,089
Detective.

531
00:46:01,300 --> 00:46:02,343
Are you scared?

532
00:46:13,104 --> 00:46:14,814
I'm fuckin' scared to death right now.

533
00:46:15,481 --> 00:46:16,941
How 'bout you?

534
00:46:23,281 --> 00:46:24,490
Yeah, me, too.

535
00:46:28,077 --> 00:46:29,745
This chitchat is useless.

536
00:46:30,288 --> 00:46:31,914
Look, if you hear a gunshot...

537
00:46:33,457 --> 00:46:35,418
...don't fuck around.
Just come right away.

538
00:46:37,962 --> 00:46:39,463
Hey, Detective.

539
00:46:40,631 --> 00:46:43,676
When I see Heeju,
I'll tell her you got out safely.

540
00:46:45,094 --> 00:46:46,929
What the hell are you talking about?

541
00:46:47,263 --> 00:46:48,306
I'll survive.

542
00:48:05,883 --> 00:48:06,967
Go look.

543
00:48:07,051 --> 00:48:08,386
Yes, sir.

544
00:48:23,734 --> 00:48:25,277
Let's see.

545
00:48:29,740 --> 00:48:30,991
Oh, shit!

546
00:48:50,719 --> 00:48:52,054
Looks good, Chairman Ahn!

547
00:48:55,099 --> 00:48:56,350
Send Kim Heeju over!

548
00:48:59,103 --> 00:49:00,104
Okay.

549
00:49:18,330 --> 00:49:19,582
We're short one?

550
00:49:19,665 --> 00:49:21,375
One is mine.
Chairman Ahn knows.

551
00:49:30,634 --> 00:49:33,137
Keep going straight
and you'll see Woogy's car.

552
00:49:33,220 --> 00:49:34,221
Get moving. Go on.

553
00:49:34,847 --> 00:49:35,848
Wait, what about you?

554
00:49:37,266 --> 00:49:38,517
What do you mean?

555
00:49:39,185 --> 00:49:40,853
Aren't you going, too?

556
00:49:41,854 --> 00:49:43,564
I can take care of myself.

557
00:49:44,482 --> 00:49:46,775
Hurry up. It's straight ahead. Go.

558
00:49:56,744 --> 00:49:58,746
Go on! Go!

559
00:50:13,010 --> 00:50:14,553
What?

560
00:50:21,852 --> 00:50:24,021
What the fuck?

561
00:50:56,428 --> 00:50:58,264
They're fake. Fuck.

562
00:50:58,347 --> 00:51:00,766
-This shit is fake, sir!
-What the hell?

563
00:51:01,684 --> 00:51:02,685
Ah, fuck!

564
00:51:03,852 --> 00:51:06,230
Why are you standing around? Go!

565
00:51:16,240 --> 00:51:17,533
Ow!

566
00:51:31,797 --> 00:51:34,341
Hurry up and get Kim Heeju!

567
00:52:28,520 --> 00:52:29,521
Let...

568
00:52:30,022 --> 00:52:33,776
Let her live the way she wants to.

569
00:52:34,735 --> 00:52:40,616
Let her go her own way.

570
00:52:40,699 --> 00:52:41,742
I just want...

571
00:52:45,496 --> 00:52:47,247
...to live a normal life.

572
00:52:50,417 --> 00:52:53,879
Just a--just a normal life.

573
00:53:21,490 --> 00:53:24,118
There aren't any cars chasing us, right?

574
00:53:24,201 --> 00:53:26,578
We did it.
Heeju, we made it out.

575
00:53:31,125 --> 00:53:32,418
The detective?

576
00:53:32,918 --> 00:53:34,169
Huh?

577
00:53:34,253 --> 00:53:35,379
Detective Kim?

578
00:53:35,462 --> 00:53:37,840
Oh, I think he drove the other direction.

579
00:53:37,923 --> 00:53:39,216
That's what we had planned.

580
00:53:41,301 --> 00:53:43,387
JEONGSAN POLICE STATION
DETECTIVE KIM JINMAN

581
00:53:43,470 --> 00:53:45,097
CALLING... JEONGSAN POLICE STATION
DETECTIVE KIM JINMAN

582
00:53:45,180 --> 00:53:46,807
Wait, are you calling him?
No, no, no, no, Heeju.

583
00:53:48,058 --> 00:53:49,768
No need for that.
He'll call us later.

584
00:53:51,311 --> 00:53:52,438
That thing down there...

585
00:53:53,564 --> 00:53:54,690
...he told me to give it to you.

586
00:53:57,443 --> 00:53:58,902
And look in the glove box, too.

587
00:54:02,489 --> 00:54:03,532
There's a gun in there.

588
00:54:04,491 --> 00:54:06,034
You should take it just in case.

589
00:54:13,459 --> 00:54:15,627
So we need to load the bars before
we head to Mokcheon.

590
00:54:16,795 --> 00:54:17,796
Where are they?

591
00:54:18,797 --> 00:54:21,258
Huh? Are they already
at Mokcheon Port, then?

592
00:54:22,968 --> 00:54:25,220
Or are they still in Jeongsan?

593
00:54:28,640 --> 00:54:29,933
Stop the car.

594
00:54:33,604 --> 00:54:34,605
Heeju.

595
00:54:36,732 --> 00:54:37,733
Pull over.

596
00:54:52,039 --> 00:54:53,123
Now get out.

597
00:54:55,167 --> 00:54:56,168
Heeju.

598
00:54:57,377 --> 00:54:58,420
Don't do this.

599
00:55:00,380 --> 00:55:02,674
I'm sorry, Woogy, but...

600
00:55:03,800 --> 00:55:05,511
...you shouldn't know where
the gold bars are.

601
00:55:08,805 --> 00:55:10,015
If it weren't for you...

602
00:55:11,433 --> 00:55:13,727
...I know there's no way I would have made
it this far.

603
00:55:15,604 --> 00:55:17,814
But you never know.
People can always change.

604
00:55:19,107 --> 00:55:20,859
I'm not gonna steal the gold, Heeju.

605
00:55:21,693 --> 00:55:22,778
I believe you.

606
00:55:24,112 --> 00:55:27,741
I really do trust you but there's still
a small chance that you could change.

607
00:56:03,652 --> 00:56:04,695
Goodbye...

608
00:56:06,154 --> 00:56:07,155
...Heeju.

609
00:56:09,408 --> 00:56:12,661
JEONGSAN CENTRAL CHURCH

610
00:58:27,212 --> 00:58:29,172
Looks like you made it just in time.

611
00:58:30,173 --> 00:58:31,842
Wait, are you alone?

612
00:58:32,801 --> 00:58:34,344
That man isn't going with you?

613
00:58:36,638 --> 00:58:37,723
I'm going alone.

614
00:58:42,352 --> 00:58:45,063
You know how it works. Money.

615
00:58:51,403 --> 00:58:52,654
There's a gold bar.

616
00:58:53,864 --> 00:58:55,031
Ten kilograms.

617
00:58:56,742 --> 00:58:58,869
It's worth about 1.5 billion won.

618
01:01:26,766 --> 01:01:33,773
THE LATE YEO SUNOK
SEPTEMBER 28, 2026

619
01:01:57,631 --> 01:01:59,716
Mom. Oh, Mom.

620
01:02:02,510 --> 01:02:03,637
Mom!

621
01:03:59,753 --> 01:04:02,797
-How much is it?
-That would be four euros, please.

622
01:04:04,215 --> 01:04:06,009
-Thank you.
-Thank you very much.

623
01:04:09,721 --> 01:04:12,057
Haran, how are you?

624
01:04:12,140 --> 01:04:14,517
That outfit looks great on you.

625
01:04:14,601 --> 01:04:17,187
Thank you. Thanks to you.

626
01:04:17,979 --> 01:04:19,898
You should come by next week again.
We'll have lots of new items.

627
01:04:19,981 --> 01:04:20,982
Yeah, okay.

628
01:04:29,783 --> 01:04:31,076
Hello.

629
01:04:31,159 --> 01:04:33,369
Come on in.
How have you been? Good?

630
01:04:33,453 --> 01:04:34,537
Yes, of course.

631
01:04:35,747 --> 01:04:37,874
Choose anything you want.
I'll pack the bread for you.

632
01:04:38,917 --> 01:04:43,505
The olive oil you gave me
the other day was amazing.

633
01:04:44,839 --> 01:04:48,510
I'll tell my wife that Ms. Ju liked
the olive oil. She'll love it.

634
01:04:48,593 --> 01:04:49,844
Yes.

635
01:04:49,928 --> 01:04:51,846
Wait, I have something for you.
Give me a second.

636
01:04:57,310 --> 01:04:59,646
I put it inside and then forgot about it.

637
01:05:00,897 --> 01:05:03,066
I should be talking less at my age.

638
01:05:03,566 --> 01:05:05,110
If I were a wise old man,
I would've known how.

639
01:05:07,028 --> 01:05:08,822
Can you carry this home?

640
01:05:08,905 --> 01:05:10,073
Of course.

641
01:05:10,406 --> 01:05:11,908
Great. Perfect.

642
01:05:12,492 --> 01:05:14,035
Thank you so much.

643
01:05:14,494 --> 01:05:20,416
No problem. Anytime for a beautiful
and kind person like you.

644
01:05:21,501 --> 01:05:22,877
-Thank you.
-Bye. Thank you.

645
01:05:23,962 --> 01:05:26,422
Hello. What a cute family.
How have you been?

646
01:07:15,406 --> 01:07:20,286
THE LATE YEO SUNOK

647
01:07:20,370 --> 01:07:27,377
THE LATE KIM JINMAN

648
01:07:30,964 --> 01:07:34,175
I RECEIVED THE WINE ALL RIGHT.
HOW ABOUT YOU?

649
01:09:02,847 --> 01:09:03,973
Hey!

650
01:09:05,099 --> 01:09:06,184
Bonjour!

651
01:09:10,104 --> 01:09:12,565
Ah, shit.

652
01:09:15,151 --> 01:09:17,320
Man, that was a long way, huh?

653
01:09:27,622 --> 01:09:28,664
You made it.

654
01:09:33,044 --> 01:09:34,045
You made it.

655
01:10:01,197 --> 01:10:03,199
Holy shit.
How big is this place?

656
01:10:12,542 --> 01:10:13,835
This is insane, right?

657
01:10:16,796 --> 01:10:17,880
Look at this!

658
01:10:21,300 --> 01:10:24,554
Is there a place like this
I could snag? Huh?

659
01:10:24,637 --> 01:10:27,598
-I don't think you can live here.
-Ah, why not?

660
01:10:27,682 --> 01:10:29,976
Just have your wine
and enjoy your time.

661
01:10:59,380 --> 01:11:06,387
THE BAKER'S WIFE

662
01:11:07,263 --> 01:11:10,683
Here's your bread, Miss Pretty Hat.

663
01:11:11,642 --> 01:11:14,645
There's a lot of sweetness
inside this bread.

664
01:11:14,729 --> 01:11:17,648
-Thank you. I'll come again.
-Thank you. Goodbye.

665
01:11:19,484 --> 01:11:20,693
Hello.

666
01:11:25,198 --> 01:11:26,574
It looks delicious.

667
01:11:27,492 --> 01:11:29,869
Once you try it, you'll want
to come back the next day.

668
01:11:34,165 --> 01:11:35,291
By the way...

669
01:11:36,250 --> 01:11:37,752
The young Asian woman.

670
01:11:38,044 --> 01:11:40,421
She's a little short
and her name is Ju Haran.

671
01:11:41,672 --> 01:11:48,679
It seems like she comes here
every now and then.

672
01:11:49,013 --> 01:11:51,098
Uh...

673
01:11:51,182 --> 01:11:52,308
I'm not sure.

674
01:11:52,767 --> 01:11:55,895
There are a lot
of Asian tourists coming here.

675
01:11:56,437 --> 01:11:57,688
I'm sorry,

676
01:11:57,772 --> 01:11:58,940
but we've been getting more

677
01:11:59,023 --> 01:12:00,316
and more young Asian
customers like you,

678
01:12:00,399 --> 01:12:02,235
coming here after hearing
about our bread.

679
01:12:02,944 --> 01:12:06,197
So I can't remember
every single one of them.

680
01:12:12,453 --> 01:12:13,788
All right.

681
01:12:14,705 --> 01:12:15,790
Thank you.
